\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs40 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid11017018\charrsid13244520 \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0        C uses some backslash characters in output functions for formating the output.These characters are called as Escape sequence characters.

\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0          In    these characters it consists of two characters ,But it is treated as  a single character.
\par \\\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 n  -  \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 new line   
\par \\\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 t  -  horizontal tab(default 8 spaces)
\par \\\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 v  -  vertical tab(default 1 line)
\par \\\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 b  -  back space
\par \\\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 a  -  alert(beep sound)  
\par \\\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 r   - Carriage return
\par \\\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 0  - null
\par \\\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 "   - double quotes
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 etc.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0\afs40 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f0\fs24\ul\insrsid11017018\charrsid13244520 
\par 
\par 
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 Program :
\par 
