\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs40 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid11017018\charrsid13244520 \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0       The process of converting from one data type to another is called as type casting or type conversion.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0         In C language type conversion is an a\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 
rithmetic expression  will be done automatically. This is called implicit conversion. If we want to store a value of one type into a variable of another type, we must caste the value to be stored by preceding it with the type name in parenthesis.This is c
