\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0\afs40 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f0\fs24\ul\insrsid11017018\charrsid13244520 \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 Syntax :
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs40 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid11017018\charrsid13244520 \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0     
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0        if\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 ( expr )
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0        \{
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0              statements;
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0        \}
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0        In this statement, first the expression will be evaluated.If it is true then the statement block will be executed and the control  transfer to the next statement. Otherwise \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 
if the expression is false, then the control directly goes to the next statement.
