\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0\afs40 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\f0\fs24\insrsid11017018\charrsid13244520 \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 To check whether the given number is even or odd 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs40 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid11017018\charrsid13244520 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 #include<s\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 tdio.h>
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 #include<conio.h>
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 void main()
\par \{
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0   int n;
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0   clrscr();
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0   printf("Enter a number : ");
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0   scanf("%d",&n);
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0   if(n%2==0)
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0     printf("Given number is Even");
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0   else
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0     printf("Given number is Odd");
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0   getch();
\par \}
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0\afs40 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f0\fs24\ul\insrsid11017018\charrsid13244520 \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 Nested if statement :
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs40 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid11017018\charrsid13244520 \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0     Using\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 
 a if statement within another if is called as nested if. If a series of decisions are involved, we use nested if statement.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0\afs40 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f0\fs24\ul\insrsid11017018\charrsid13244520 \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 Form : 1
