\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0\afs40 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f0\fs24\ul\insrsid11017018\charrsid13244520 \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 Switch    statement :
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs40 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid11017018\charrsid13244520 \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0     It is a multiway conditional control statement used in C language. It is mainly used in situa\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 
tions where there is need to pick one alternative among many alternatives.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af44\afs40 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f44\fs24\ul\insrsid11017018\charrsid13244520 \hich\af44\dbch\af31505\loch\f44 Syntax :
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af44\afs40 \ltrch\fcs0 \f44\fs24\insrsid11017018\charrsid13244520 \hich\af44\dbch\af31505\loch\f44   }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af44\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f44\fs20\insrsid11017018\charrsid13244520 \hich\af44\dbch\af31505\loch\f44 
switch(variable / expression)
\par \hich\af44\dbch\af31505\loch\f44     \{
\par \hich\af44\dbch\af31505\loch\f44             case   value-1 :
\par \hich\af44\dbch\af31505\loch\f44                                   statements \hich\f44 \endash \loch\f44  1;
\par \hich\af44\dbch\af31505\loch\f44                                   break;    
\par 
\par \hich\af44\dbch\af31505\loch\f44          \hich\af44\dbch\af31505\loch\f44    case  value-2 :
\par \hich\af44\dbch\af31505\loch\f44                                     statements \hich\f44 \endash \loch\f44  2;
\par \hich\af44\dbch\af31505\loch\f44                                      break;       
\par \hich\af44\dbch\af31505\loch\f44 \hich\f44             \'85\'85\'85\'85\'85\'85\'85\'85..
\par \hich\af44\dbch\af31505\loch\f44 \hich\f44              \'85\'85\'85\'85\'85\'85\'85\'85.
\par \hich\af44\dbch\af31505\loch\f44             case  value-n :
\par \hich\af44\dbch\af31505\loch\f44                                 statements \hich\f44 \endash \loch\f44  n;
\par \hich\af44\dbch\af31505\loch\f44  \hich\af44\dbch\af31505\loch\f44                                break;       
\par \hich\af44\dbch\af31505\loch\f44            default :
\par \hich\af44\dbch\af31505\loch\f44                          default statements;
\par \hich\af44\dbch\af31505\loch\f44        \}
\par 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af44\afs40 \ltrch\fcs0 \f44\fs24\insrsid11017018\charrsid13244520 \hich\af44\dbch\af31505\loch\f44    The switch statement tests the value of given variable or expression against a list of case values. When a match is found, the stat
\hich\af44\dbch\af31505\loch\f44 ement associated to that case is executed and the control transfer to the next statement, otherwise the default statements will be executed.
\par \hich\af44\dbch\af31505\loch\f44   }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs40 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid11017018\charrsid13244520 
