      C language permits the usage of limited input and output functions to read and write data. These functions are used for only smaller volume of data and it b\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 
ecomes difficult to handle longer data volumes. Also the entire data is lost when the program over.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0      To overcome these difficulties a flexible method was developed by employing the concept of files to store, to read and write data and to return them ev\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 en when the program over.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0\afs40 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f0\fs24\ul\insrsid11017018\charrsid13244520 \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 Definition :
